<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="131" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4480: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-14T00:00:00+01:00">July 14, 1931—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received July
                                        15—5:16 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>84. Reference is made to my telegram No. 82, July 14, 6 p.m. The
                                    Belgian Government is now working out a formula for notification
                                    to the B. I. S. of provisional postponement of German payments
                                    tomorrow.</p>
                                <pb facs="0300" n="186" xml:id="pg_186"/>
                                <p>The Belgian Government has formally accepted the British
                                    invitation to the London Conference and is sending a delegation
                                    tomorrow.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>